VMusic fest at Thanjavur
p3
sVnews
p4
VG. SRINIVASANA 10-day  music festival organised under the auspices of Sri Thyagabrahma Sabha at Sri Besant Lodge is now  on  (till July 1)  at Thanjavur. Inaugurating the festival, Dr. C.Subramaniam, vice-chancellor of Tamil University called upon the musicians t\u000ao popularise Thamizh Isai. &#8220;At the same time we should also appreciate  music in other languages. Abraham Pandithar was a famous composer in Tamil. He wroteKarnamkirthasaharam, a book on music which formed the basis of  many mu\u000asic books. Thus, Thanjavur was a pioneer in music,&#8221; Subramaniam said.G.Swaminathan, former MP, called for  the translation of Tyagaraja&#8217;s kritis  into Tamil. &#8220;Thyagabrahma Sabha will support such a move, if initiated  by the Tamil University,&#8221; he said.The festival started with  nagaswaram music by Mannargudi M.S.K.Shankaranarayanan,  M.S.K.Venkatesan and party. Thanjavur T.R.Govindarajan was on the special thavil and Mettupalayam M.S.Ravikumar on the thavil.  Nagamani Srinath&#8217;s vocal recital followed on  Saturday. A special music programme, &#8216;Laya ensemble&#8217; was conducted on Sunday by  Karaikudi R.Mani.  While Karaikudi R.Mani played the mridangam,  B.V.Balasai  was on the flute, U.P.Raju on the mandolin and V. Suresh on the ghatam.  Mani enthralled the audience and kept them spellbound for three hours.  On Monday, Aiswarya Raghavan began her vocal recital with  Oothukadu Venkatasubbaiyer&#8217;s &#8216;Sri Vignarajambhaje,&#8217;  She also sang  Tyagaraja&#8217;s &#8216;Ganamoorthe.&#8217;  She was at  her best when she sang &#8216;Thiruvadi Charanam&#8217;.Udayalur Kalayanaraman&#8217;s namasankeertanam,  Girija Ramaswamy&#8217;s harikatha   T.N.Seshagopalan&#8217;s recital,  lecture demonstrations and competitions formed part of the event.The coming week will feature Kumaravayalur Thirugnana Balachandra Othuvar&#8217;s thevaram,  Nisha Rajagopal&#8217;s  Divya Prabandham  T.V.Sankaranarayanan&#8217;s vocal  and Swarnamalya&#8217;s dance recital.Bottom Template Starts
